# Coordinate Converter — Domain Knowledge (On Demand)

## Coordinate / GIS domain
- App is a lightweight GIS tool: parsing + conversions + mini-map + tools.
- Coordinate formats include: WGS84 (DD/DDM/DMS), UTM, MGRS, Plus Codes.
- There are Italian datums and additional datum support introduced later (see below).

## Datum / CRS additions (implemented)
- Extra datum section exists in results (collapsible):
  - NAD27 / NAD83 / OSGB36 / CH1903 / SK42 (as implemented in the HTML).
- Auto-detect extended for:
  - BNG (British National Grid)
  - SK42 Gauss–Krüger
- Export toggle exists to include datum extras as metadata/extensions in GPX/KML/GeoJSON.

## DTG NATO (Date-Time Group)
- Full support for DTG format: `DDHHMMZMMMYY` (e.g. `211630ZAPR26`).
- Parsing/formatting is implemented without external deps; `J` timezone letter is intentionally rejected.
- Keyboard shortcuts prefer `Alt+T` / `Alt+Shift+T` due to browser conflicts with `Ctrl+T`.
- DTG is stored as **Zulu** in history/favorites/exports to avoid ambiguity.

## Geocoding (OPSEC-aware)
- Forward geocoding and reverse geocoding exist, using Nominatim.
- Strict/OPSEC mode exists (`state.opsecStrict`): must block any external fetch.
- Defensive UX patterns:
  - geocode UI is closed by default; opening implies consent to read the disclaimer
  - no silent exfiltration: non-coordinate paste prompts explicit `confirm()` before searching online
- Resilience:
  - client-side rate limiting (≈ 1 request / second)
  - retry with backoff
  - circuit breaker (temporary lockout after repeated failures)
- Offline fallback exists via a small built-in cities dataset + optional user-imported JSON stored in IDB.

## Offline map tiles / coverage overlay
- IndexedDB tile pack exists; when offline, the mini-map renders cached tiles and uses placeholders for missing tiles.
- Coverage overlay exists:
  - per-tile green tint when tile is served from IDB cache
  - named areas overlay rectangles with zoom-range signaling
- Named areas include bbox + optional zoom range `z0..z1` (legacy entries without `z0/z1` must keep working).
- Offline panel can dock/floating depending on map size; it can be draggable in full mode.
- Deleting a named area can optionally delete tiles from IDB (supports wiping both map layers if layer is not tracked per pack).

## Tools drawer / navigation hub
- Tools drawer is a navigation hub: it scrolls to existing `<details>` tool sections in `<main>` and flashes/highlights them.
- Do not refactor it into a “workspace drawer”; keep main sections in the DOM.

## Track builder
- Track builder exists with:
  - add current result, click map pick mode, paste list, import GPX/KML/GeoJSON
  - export GPX/KML/GeoJSON/CSV
- `Esc` exits pick modes before doing global clear actions.

## Map measurement
- On-map measurement supports:
  - line (distance + azimuth)
  - polygon (perimeter + area)
  - drag handles + right-click delete
  - units (m/km/nm/mi/ft) persisted in storage
